def train_model(classifier, feature_vector_train, label, feature_vector_valid, method):
    
    # train classification
    classifier.fit(feature_vector_train, label)
    
    # prediction on test
    predictions = classifier.predict(feature_vector_valid)
    
    # report
    print(classification_report(y_test, predictions))
    
    # confusion matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(predictions, y_test)
    #print(cm)
    cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    cax = ax.matshow(cm, cmap=cmap)
    fig.colorbar(cax)

    plt.title('Confusion matrix of ' + method, pad=40)
    #ax.set_xticklabels([''] + shortfilename, rotation=45)
    #ax.set_yticklabels([''] + shortfilename)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('True')
    plt.show()
    
    return metrics.accuracy_score(predictions, y_test)

from tqdm import tqdm
new_pattern = []
for item in tqdm(zero_zero.itertuples(), desc="New Pattern"):
    temp = item.Pattern.split(" ")
    temp_pattern = ""
    for word in temp:
        if word not in stop:
            temp_pattern = temp_pattern + word + " "
    temp_pattern = temp_pattern[:-1]
    new_pattern.append(temp_pattern)

%%time
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(zero_zero["Pattern"], zero_zero["Class"], 
                                                    stratify = zero_zero["Class"], random_state = 0)

xtest_tfidf =  tfidf_vect.transform(X_test)

from collections import Counter
classes = dict(Counter(y_train))
classes2 = list(sorted(classes.items()))
mean = int(len(y_train)/len(classes))

label = []
samples = []
i = 0
for i in range(len(classes2)):
    label.append(classes2[i][0])
    if (i == 0) or ((i) % 3 == 0):
        if (i+2 < len(classes2)):
            samples.append(max(classes2[i+1][1], classes2[i+2][1]))
    else:
        samples.append(classes2[i][1])
        
classes = dict(zip(label, samples))

from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=0, sampling_strategy=classes)
ros_xtrain_tfidf, ros_y_train = ros.fit_sample(xtrain_tfidf, y_train)

2.2.1 Resampling¶

In [111]:
classes = dict(Counter(y_train))
classes2 = list(sorted(classes.items()))
mean = int(len(y_train)/len(classes))

label = []
samples = []
i = 0
for i in range(len(classes2)):
    label.append(classes2[i][0])
    if (i == 0) or ((i) % 3 == 0):
        if (i+2 < len(classes2)):
            samples.append(max(classes2[i+1][1], classes2[i+2][1]))
    else:
        samples.append(classes2[i][1])
        
classes = dict(zip(label, samples))

from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=0, sampling_strategy=classes)
ros_xtrain_tfidf, ros_y_train = ros.fit_sample(xtrain_tfidf, y_train)

2.3.1 Resampling¶

In [130]:
classes = dict(Counter(y_train))
classes2 = list(sorted(classes.items()))
mean = int(len(y_train)/len(classes))

label = []
samples = []
i = 0
for i in range(len(classes2)):
    label.append(classes2[i][0])
    if (i == 0) or ((i) % 3 == 0):
        if (i+2 < len(classes2)):
            samples.append(max(classes2[i+1][1], classes2[i+2][1]))
    else:
        samples.append(classes2[i][1])
        
classes = dict(zip(label, samples))

from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=0, sampling_strategy=classes)
ros_xtrain_tfidf, ros_y_train = ros.fit_sample(xtrain_tfidf, y_train)

    if (i == 0) or ((i) % 3 == 0):
        if (i+2 < len(classes2)):
            samples.append(max(classes2[i+1][1], classes2[i+2][1]))
    else:
        samples.append(classes2[i][1])
        
classes = dict(zip(label, samples))

from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler
ros = RandomOverSampler(random_state=0, sampling_strategy=classes)
ros_xtrain_tfidf, ros_y_train = ros.fit_sample(xtrain_tfidf, y_train)
